This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as event and temporal relation extraction. Additionally, the use of neural representation learning and structured prediction methods are common in this sub-category. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed model involves machine learning techniques for information extraction. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses shared representation learning and structured prediction, which are common topics in machine learning research. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possibility as the paper involves the use of neural networks for representation learning. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely but still possible sub-category as the paper deals with extracting information from text data.
